        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap) across MiniMax image-generation, OAuth, TTS, and video-generation providers (6 call sites in 4 files).\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Unit tests\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/\n  Test Files  9 passed (9)\n       Tests  81 passed (81)\n```\n\n### Real HTTP proof (against live server)\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run test/proof-bounded-json.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n\nstdout | real behavior proof: bounded JSON response reads\n  ✅ Normal JSON: 51 bytes parsed successfully from real HTTP\n\nstdout | real behavior proof: bounded JSON response reads\n  ✅ Oversized JSON correctly rejected — overflow error thrown before OOM\n\nstdout | real behavior proof: bounded JSON response reads\n  ✅ Stream cancelled early — rejected in 41ms (not waiting for full 2.5 MiB)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  3 passed (3)\n```\n\nThe proof harness uses a real HTTP server (not mocked Response objects).\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
